# Swaps Form UI Conventions

## Inline-left labels (`_lrow`)

**All** form inputs must render their label to the left, inline with the widget.  
Use `_lrow()` + `label_visibility="collapsed"` — never put a label above an input.

```python
# ❌ BAD — label renders above
st.selectbox("Curve", options=..., key=...)

# ✅ GOOD — label renders to the left
_lrow("Curve").selectbox("", options=..., key=..., label_visibility="collapsed")
```

`_lrow` signature: `def _lrow(label: str, ratio: tuple[int, int] = (1, 2)) -> DeltaGenerator`

## Widget keys

Every template-dependent widget key must start with `fk = f"{tab_key}_{spec_key}"` so
switching templates forces Streamlit to mount a fresh widget.

```python
# ❌ BAD — same key across templates means value never resets
st.selectbox("...", key=f"{tab_key}_maturity")

# ✅ GOOD — template switch changes the key, widget resets
st.selectbox("...", key=f"{fk}_maturity")
```

Display-only (disabled) widgets must embed their current value in the key to avoid
`StreamlitDuplicateElementId` and ensure dynamic re-renders:

```python
st.text_input("", value=effective, key=f"{tab_key}_effective_leg2_{effective}", disabled=True, ...)
```

## Curves (`_curve_selectbox`)

Always use `_curve_selectbox(label, default_id, key)` — never inline a curve selectbox.

Layout: **two** curve columns per leg (Leg 1 and Leg 2), matching the XCCY pattern.  
OIS and XCCY must use the same per-leg layout.

## Solve-for dropdown

Fetch targets dynamically via `_get_solve_targets(deal_type)` — never hardcode lists.

```python
_solve_targets = _get_solve_targets(spec.deal_type)
solve_for = _lrow(t("swaps.solve_for_label")).selectbox(
    "", options=_solve_targets, key=f"{fk}_solve_for", label_visibility="collapsed"
)
```

## Service cache invalidation

When changing `SwapPricingService`, increment `_SVC_VERSION` in `pages/swaps.py`
to bust the `@st.cache_resource` instance.
